</caption>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="278" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1447,1904]" pageId="7" pageNumber="278">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1447,1472]" pageId="7" pageNumber="278">Description.</emphasis>
Total body length 
<quantity box="[560,699,1447,1471]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0999999999999996" metricValueMax="2.3" metricValueMin="1.9" pageId="7" pageNumber="278" unit="mm" value="2.0999999999999996" valueMax="2.3" valueMin="1.9">1.9–2.3 mm</quantity>
. Dorsal coloration light brown to yellow (
<figureCitation box="[1176,1245,1447,1472]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1936,1958]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,555,1914]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,555,1914]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Habitus of Globulosis spp. G. hemisphericus (from Suriname): (A) dorsal, (B) lateral, (C) ventral; G. flavus (paratype): (D) dorsal, (E) lateral, (F) ventral. Scale bar 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/293122/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="278">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
D). Thoracic and abdominal venter brown to dark brown (
<figureCitation box="[607,669,1483,1508]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1936,1958]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,555,1914]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,555,1914]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Habitus of Globulosis spp. G. hemisphericus (from Suriname): (A) dorsal, (B) lateral, (C) ventral; G. flavus (paratype): (D) dorsal, (E) lateral, (F) ventral. Scale bar 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/293122/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="278">Fig 2</figureCitation>
F). Maxillary palps uniformly yellow (
<figureCitation box="[1104,1171,1483,1508]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,961,983]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,193,944]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[189,1398,193,944]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Head in frontal view of Globulosis spp. (A) G. hemisphericus, (B) G. flavus. Scale bar: 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/292831/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="278">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
B). Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[1340,1407,1483,1508]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1319,1341]" captionTargetBox="[163,1423,755,1284]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,738,1297]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 7. Aedeagus of Globulosis spp. (A) G. flavus sp. n. (holotype), (B) G. hemisphericus, reproduced from García, 2001, (C) G. hemisphericus from the upper Berbice, Guyana, (D) G. hemisphericus from Manaus, Brazil, (E) G. hemisphericus from Raleighvallen Nature Reserve, Suriname. Scale bar 0.05 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/292835/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="278">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
A) with basal piece short, less than one third the length of the parameres; outer margins of parameres parallel-sided, with apex slightly curved inward. Median lobe broad, narrowing in apical third to an acute point, apex slightly lower than the apex of the parameres; gonopore situated in apical third.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,926,1627,1652]" pageId="7" pageNumber="278" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1447,1904]" box="[199,926,1627,1652]" pageId="7" pageNumber="278">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1627,1652]" pageId="7" pageNumber="278">Etymology.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[340,407,1627,1652]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Globulosis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="278" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavus">
<emphasis box="[340,407,1627,1652]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="278">flavus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, L., after the yellow coloration of the dorsum.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="278" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1447,1904]" pageId="7" pageNumber="278">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,1663,1688]" pageId="7" pageNumber="278">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[359,474,1663,1688]" name="Venezuela" pageId="7" pageNumber="278">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[490,613,1663,1687]" country="Venezuela" name="Amazonas" pageId="7" pageNumber="278">Amazonas</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[624,697,1664,1688]" country="Venezuela" name="Apure" pageId="7" pageNumber="278">Apure</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[708,797,1663,1688]" country="Venezuela" name="Bolivar" pageId="7" pageNumber="278">Bolívar</collectingRegion>
). The specimen from 
<collectingRegion box="[1042,1115,1664,1688]" country="Venezuela" name="Apure" pageId="7" pageNumber="278">Apure</collectingRegion>
, though in the llanos, was in a morichal (palm-lined stream) very close to the Orinoco River in an area that has an Amazonian influence.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1213,1735,1760]" pageId="7" pageNumber="278" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1447,1904]" box="[199,1213,1735,1760]" pageId="7" pageNumber="278">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,295,1735,1760]" pageId="7" pageNumber="278">Biology.</emphasis>
This species has been collected along the margins of lotic habitats (e.g., 
<figureCitation box="[1111,1177,1735,1760]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1253,1275]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,267,1231]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,267,1231]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 9. Habitat of Globulosis sp. (A) Venezuela: Pijiguaos, collecting event VZ 09 - 0112 - 01 A, (B) Suriname: Kasikasima, collecting event SR 12 - 0320 - 02 A, (C) Suriname: Raleighvallen, collecting event SR 12 - 0727 - 03 A, (D) Suriname: near Kutari River, collecting event SR 12 - 0727 - 03 A." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/292837/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="278">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
A).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="278" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1447,1904]" pageId="7" pageNumber="278">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1771,1796]" pageId="7" pageNumber="278">Remarks.</emphasis>
The northwest “shoulder” of the 
<collectingCountry box="[693,774,1771,1796]" name="Guyana" pageId="7" pageNumber="278">Guiana</collectingCountry>
Shield where this species occurs has been found to harbor unique lineages of aquatic insects that have not been found elsewhere in the region, including 
<taxonomicName authority="Spangler &amp; Steiner 2005" authorityName="Spangler &amp; Steiner" authorityYear="2005" class="Insecta" family="Meruidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="278" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">
Meruidae (
<bibRefCitation author="Spangler" pageId="7" pageNumber="278" refString="Spangler, P. J. &amp; Steiner, W. E. Jr. (2005) A new aquatic beetle family, Meruidae, from Venezuela (Coleoptera: Adephaga). Systematic Entomology, 30, 339 - 357." type="journal article" year="2005">Spangler &amp; Steiner 2005</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and a lineage of 
<taxonomicName authority="Short et al. 2015" authorityName="Short et al." authorityYear="2015" box="[533,935,1843,1868]" class="Insecta" family="Hydroscaphidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="278" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">
Hydroscaphidae (
<bibRefCitation author="Short" box="[731,927,1843,1868]" pageId="7" pageNumber="278" refString="Short, A. E. Z., Joly, L. J., Garcia, M., Wild, A., Bloom, D. D. &amp; Maddison, D. R. (2015) Molecular phylogeny of the Hydroscaphidae (Coleoptera: Myxophaga) with description of a remarkable new lineage from the Guiana Shield. Systematic Entomology, 40, 214 - 229." type="journal article" year="2015">Short et al. 2015</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. The reason for this apparent biogeographic distinctness is not well understood.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
